/// Multi-Head Latent Attention (MLA)
///
/// DeepSeek-V2/V3's key attention innovation. Compresses key-value pairs
/// into a low-rank latent representation, dramatically reducing KV cache
/// memory (93% reduction reported in DeepSeek-V2).
///
/// Instead of caching full K,V per layer, MLA:
/// 1. Projects input to a low-rank latent: c_kv = W_dkv(x) — shape [batch, seq, kv_lora_rank]
/// 2. Decompresses per-head for attention: K = W_uk(c_kv), V = W_uv(c_kv)
/// 3. Query also optionally compressed: c_q = W_dq(x) — shape [batch, seq, q_lora_rank]
/// 4. Performs standard scaled dot-product attention with RoPE on a subset of dims
///
/// Parameters:
/// - dim: Model hidden dimension
/// - num_heads: Number of attention heads
/// - kv_lora_rank: Latent dimension for KV compression
/// - q_lora_rank: Latent dimension for query compression (0 = no compression)
/// - v_head_dim: Value head dimension
///
/// Shape Contract:
/// - Input: [batch, seq, dim]
/// - Output: [batch, seq, dim]
///
/// Reference: DeepSeek-V2 (2024) "DeepSeek-V2: A Strong, Economical, and
/// Efficient Mixture-of-Experts Language Model"
neuron MultiHeadLatentAttention(dim, num_heads, kv_lora_rank, q_lora_rank, v_head_dim):
    in: [batch, seq, dim]
    out: [batch, seq, dim]
    impl: neuroscript,attention/MultiHeadLatentAttention
